Ceremony Style

The Lover's Kiss
Presided over by a choir moogle, this ceremony is conducted in a light-hearted fashion and is sealed with a kiss.

The Spinner's Hand
Presided over by a female Officiant of the Graces, this traditional ceremony dedicated to the Twelve concludes with a symbolic toast to mark the start of your lives together.

The Solemn Oath
Presided over by a male Officiant of the Vows, this undenominational ceremony closes with the signing of an official pact before the assembled guests.

Chapel Decoration

※<If(LessThan(IntegerParameter(1),2))>Natural lighting will be used in the chapel<Else/>You may choose between natural or romantic lighting options for the chapel</If>.

PvP (player versus player) duty involves battles fought against other players rather than in-game creatures and incorporates an independent battle system with its own set of unique rules. FINAL FANTASY XIV offers several different varieties of PvP from ranked matches to casual training for anywhere from 2 to 72 participants.

For more information on PvP, visit the Lodestone─the official player's site for FINAL FANTASY XIV.
Use the code reader application on your smartphone and access the Lodestone to view the PvP page.

Crystal bells found throughout Eorzea can be used to summon an aesthetician.
Private chambers can now be added to free company estates.
Members with personal chambers can now be discharged from free companies. Any items kept within the chambers can be reclaimed by speaking with a resident caretaker.
You can now change the color of your stabled chocobo's plumage by feeding him snacks.
You can now purchase land for a private estate. Speak with a resident caretaker for a detailed explanation on the steps required.
Subdivisions have been added to all three residential districts. There are now double the amount of plots available for purchase. Travel to the subdivisions is possible via Aethernet shards.
You can now use expansion of duty permits, allowing the dispatchment of retainers on estate property. Speak with a resident caretaker for a detailed explanation on the steps required.
You can now use aetherial wheels. Charge wheels on wheel stands and convert the stored energy into company actions. Speak with a resident caretaker for a detailed explanation on the steps required.

You can now add a company workshop to your estate. Workshops can be used to craft company projects such as aetherial wheels, housing materials, and airships. Those airships can then be deployed on exploratory voyages. Speak with a resident caretaker for a detailed explanation on the steps required.
A new attraction─the Lord of Verminion─is now available in Chocobo Square!

The following changes have been made to housing:

 - Estate sharing is now available with private estates.
 - The brightness of estate lighting can now be adjusted.
 - Estates not accessed for extended periods of time will be automatically demolished and the plots of land put back up for sale.

For further details on these changes, speak with a <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>resident caretaker<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>.

Exploratory missions are now available through the company workshop's <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>voyage control panel<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>. These missions allow you and your company members to explore a remote cluster of islets in the Sea of Clouds known as the Diadem.

For further details, speak with the mammet voyager #004A.

Flowerpots and flower vases are now available for placement in all private estates and chambers. Curious crops grown in the flowerpots can be exchanged for materials at residential area material suppliers.

<UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>Apartments<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> are now available for purchase in residential areas. Speak with a resident caretaker for details.

The following activities have been added to the Duty Finder and are accessible under Gold Saucer:

<UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>Triple Triad Battlehall Matches<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
<UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>LoVM Player Battles (Non-RP)<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>

Lord of Verminion match registration no longer requires MGP.

The following features have been added to estate orchestrions:

<UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>Playlists<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
<UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>Play All option<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>

Further information on playlists can be found under the active help topic “The Orchestrion.”

Caught fish can now be placed in <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>aquariums<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> and displayed in estates or private rooms.
Paintings are now available for purchase at the Hard Place in Idyllshire. These paintings can be placed in frames and displayed in personal estates, rooms, and apartments.

New exploratory missions are now available through the company workshop's <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>voyage control panel<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>. These missions allow you and your company members to explore a remote cluster of islets in the Sea of Clouds known as the Diadem.

For further details, speak with the mammet voyager #004A.

A <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>relocation<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> option is now available to estate owners wishing to move to a new plot of land. In addition, owners will now be granted use of <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>storerooms<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> for the temporary storage of both outdoor and indoor furnishings. Speak with a resident caretaker for details.

Unsure what to wear to the coming seasonal event? <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>Glamour dressers<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> have been added to inn rooms in all of Eorzea's major city–states and Kugane, making gear coordination even easier!

Custom <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>PvP teams<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> can now be formed! View the <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>team creation board<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> located on the <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>Wolves' Den Pier<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> to learn more!

The following temporary <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>restrictions<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> have
been placed on future land purchases:

・All new land purchases are limited to <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>free companies<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>.
・Players may only own one private and one free company estate per <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>World<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> per <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>service account<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>.
・Free companies with less than <UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>four members<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> cannot purchase land.

<UIForeground>F20202</UIForeground>Party Progress<UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
A party's starting point in the raid is
determined by the leader's past progress.
As long as all other conditions are met, 
players who have not progressed as far as
the leader may still participate in the duty.

If a party member's progress was less
than that of the leader, then progress
will be updated to match.

If a party member's progress is beyond
that of the leader, that member's progress
will remain unaffected.

<UIForeground>F20202</UIForeground>Reward Restrictions<UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Players will not earn rewards for completing
phases they have already completed.
Coffer quantity will vary based on the total
number of party members who have already
completed the duty.

When participating in the latest Savage raid
with a matched party, duty rewards may
change based on the progress level of
matched members.

<UIForeground>F20202</UIForeground>Job Distribution<UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Parties formed with the Raid Finder do not
allow for two members with the same job
unless certain conditions are met.

DPS jobs are divided into the following roles:
Melee DPS, Ranged Physical DPS,
Ranged Magic DPS, and Not Specified.

When the raid purpose is set as “Duty Completion,”
the jobs that fall into Not Specified must be
different from the ones which fill the other three
DPS roles. When the raid purpose is set to “Practice,”
overlapping between specified and unspecified DPS
jobs is allowed.

from current Duty Finder settings.

<UIForeground>F20202</UIForeground>Penalties<UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Penalties for withdrawing from duties are
shared between all matched content.

Use the board not only to create your very own PvP team,
but to view information on how teams are formed and rated.

PvP teams are adventurers who, rather than have their companions
chosen at random, have joined together to take on the Feast and other
PvP duties in custom-made parties of their own creation.

The strength of a team can be gauged by its rating. Similar to an
individual's PvP rating, team rating is affected by participating in
ranked matches. Prizes and tournament eligibility are awarded at the
end of each season to the teams which emerge with the highest ratings.

To create a PvP team, the following conditions must be met:
・Only a party leader can create a team
・Members cannot be part of another PvP team
・Parties must have 4-6 members (crossworld allowed)
・All members must have unlocked PvP
・Players on free trial accounts are not allowed

Team rating is a numerical value that indicates the relative strength of
a PvP team. This value will increase or decrease based on performance
in ranked matches. To register for a PvP team-specific ranked match,
a party of 4 members from the same PvP team must first be formed.

Team rank is determined by a team's current rating.
Rank will rise and fall as the team's rating does.

“Season” is the term used to indicate the fixed period of time during
which official team and solo PvP matches are held. Only participating
in ranked matches during a season will contribute to your PvP rating.
Teams which end the season with the highest rankings are awarded
special prizes and granted eligibility to exclusive tournaments.
Team ratings and rankings are reset at the end of every season.
Season schedule and ranking information can be viewed under
<UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>PvP Team<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> in the <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>main menu<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>.

Team information, including status of current members, can be viewed
under <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>PvP Team<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> in the <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>main menu<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>.

To invite a player to a PvP team, target him or her and select <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>Invite
to PvP Team<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> from the subcommands. The invitee will join the
team upon agreeing to the request. To invite someone from another
World server to your PvP team, you must first be in a cross-world
party with that player.

Dismissing a member of your PvP team is conducted in the same
manner as invitations, except <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>Dismiss from PvP Team<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> is chosen from
the subcommands after targeting the player. Only PvP team leaders
or subleaders may invite and dismiss members.

<UIForeground>F201FA</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FB</UIGlow>Once a PvP season has begun, you may not recruit new members
to your team. If, during a season, member count falls below four,
your team will be removed from the rankings.<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>

Certain team actions, such as changing the team name or updating the
team crest, require authorization to execute. This authorization is only
granted to team leaders and subleaders. A team subleader can be
appointed by the team leader via subcommand on the member list in
the PvP Team interface.

To disband a team, the leader must first select the option <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>Disband
Team<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> found under <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>Status<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> on the PvP Team interface. More than half of
the team members must then agree to the disbandment before it is
executed. Team history, rank, and rating are all deleted upon
disbandment.

To leave a PvP team, a member must select <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>Leave Team<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>, also found
under <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>Status<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground> on the PvP Team interface. Once the team has been left,
that member will no longer have access to functions and content
associated with the former PvP team.

If a leader is not online for more than 90 days (including cases where
the character has been deleted), the PvP team's subleader will be
automatically promoted to leader. If the team does not have an
appointed subleader, the title of leader will be assigned to the
member who joined the team first.
A PvP team will automatically be disbanded if no members log in for more than 90 days (Earth time).

Any player can create a cross-world linkshell, as well as join one via invite. While communication between players on the same world is possible through cross-world linkshells, it is recommended that intra-world communication is done using normal linkshells available in Limsa Lominsa, Gridania, and Ul'dah.

Please note, players may only belong to one cross-world linkshell at a time, and linkshells with less than 2 active members will be automatically disbanded if new members are not added within 24 hours (Earth time). Multiple cross-world linkshells cannot be created in succession.
